1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,500
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

2
00:00:03,500 --> 00:00:07,040
No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.

3
00:00:07,040 --> 00:00:09,540
Oh! Okay, fine.

4
00:00:09,540 --> 00:00:13,540
Ryan, something the matter?

5
00:00:13,540 --> 00:00:15,380
Smokey's dead.

6
00:00:15,380 --> 00:00:17,580
Smokey the Bear?

7
00:00:17,580 --> 00:00:19,180
Smokey Robinson. Pam.

8
00:00:19,180 --> 00:00:20,720
He died, like, an hour ago.

9
00:00:20,720 --> 00:00:22,380
I guess I'm the first to know.

10
00:00:22,380 --> 00:00:24,720
Wow, that's terrible. I really liked him.

11
00:00:24,720 --> 00:00:26,720
Oh, you liked him? That's nice.

12
00:00:26,720 --> 00:00:29,060
Did you like when he changed the course of American music

13
00:00:29,080 --> 00:00:30,260
like two or three times?

14
00:00:30,260 --> 00:00:32,260
Did you like the tracks of my tears?

15
00:00:32,260 --> 00:00:34,720
Is maybe the last true love song ever written?

16
00:00:34,720 --> 00:00:36,220
I'm glad you like him, Jim.

17
00:00:36,220 --> 00:00:38,560
I am completely devastated right now.

18
00:00:38,560 --> 00:00:40,700
Well, I second that emotion.

19
00:00:40,700 --> 00:00:41,940
Huh?

20
00:00:41,940 --> 00:00:43,740
I know a few of his songs, but what were his big ones?

21
00:00:43,740 --> 00:00:46,140
Oh, God, Nellie, what wasn't his?

22
00:00:46,140 --> 00:00:48,240
I mean, um, tracks of my tears?

23
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:49,340
Yeah.

24
00:00:49,340 --> 00:00:50,980
Um, God, so many, Nellie.

25
00:00:50,980 --> 00:00:52,340
No, no, no, no.

26
00:00:52,340 --> 00:00:54,440
Tracks of my tears and what else?

27
00:00:54,440 --> 00:00:57,780
What are some more? What's one more?

28
00:00:58,540 --> 00:01:00,940
Okay, I'm not playing this game, Pam.

29
00:01:00,940 --> 00:01:02,140
Not today.

30
00:01:02,140 --> 00:01:03,780
I don't think you love Smokey Robinson.

31
00:01:03,780 --> 00:01:05,240
I think you're just doing all of this

32
00:01:05,240 --> 00:01:06,980
to prove how deep you are about music.

33
00:01:06,980 --> 00:01:09,720
Okay, I'm sorry that I'm not a fan of Jason Mraz

34
00:01:09,720 --> 00:01:10,920
or The Beatles.

35
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:12,180
You don't like The Beatles?

36
00:01:12,180 --> 00:01:13,420
That's not the point.

37
00:01:13,420 --> 00:01:14,980
Eleanor Rigby, paperback writer?

38
00:01:14,980 --> 00:01:16,260
Okay, you know, you always think you have time

39
00:01:16,260 --> 00:01:17,660
to see these legends before they go.

40
00:01:17,660 --> 00:01:19,120
What was I so busy doing?

41
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:22,260
It says here the Smokey Robinson dead thing is a hoax.

42
00:01:22,260 --> 00:01:25,000
It's on CNN as of two minutes ago.

43
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:28,560
Okay, well, that's a relief.

44
00:01:28,560 --> 00:01:29,860
Wow, look at that.

45
00:01:29,860 --> 00:01:31,760
It says he's actually playing state college.

46
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:33,660
It's only three hours away.

47
00:01:33,660 --> 00:01:36,400
Oh, my God, Ryan, that's perfect.

48
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:37,700
You have to go.

49
00:01:37,700 --> 00:01:39,540
Tickets are 250 bucks.

50
00:01:39,540 --> 00:01:44,880
$250 is nothing to the world's biggest Smokey Robinson fan.

51
00:01:44,880 --> 00:01:46,880
Yeah.

52
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:48,380
Who's opening?

53
00:01:48,380 --> 00:01:51,380
Paul Enka. Paul Enka?

54
00:01:51,380 --> 00:01:54,180
How can they make the Smokeman play with someone like that?

55
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,840
I don't think I can see this.

56
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:57,300
Okay, he could just show up late, though.

57
00:01:57,300 --> 00:01:58,980
How much is parking? Like, 30 bucks?

58
00:01:58,980 --> 00:02:00,940
That's not what Smokey would have wanted.

59
00:02:00,940 --> 00:02:02,380
Does want.

60
00:02:02,380 --> 00:02:03,380
Tears of a clown.

61
00:02:03,380 --> 00:02:05,080
Don't call me a clown, Pam.

62
00:02:05,080 --> 00:02:07,080
You're better than that.

63
00:02:11,060 --> 00:02:14,060
["Sweet Home Alone"]

64
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:23,560
Looking good, RC.

65
00:02:23,580 --> 00:02:25,220
Ugh, I hate ties.

66
00:02:25,220 --> 00:02:26,820
I feel like I'm being strangled,

67
00:02:26,820 --> 00:02:29,820
like I'm at some erotic asphyxiation sex club

68
00:02:29,820 --> 00:02:33,460
over on I-84, the Red Room, say, or Dominic's.

69
00:02:33,460 --> 00:02:36,260
Robert, the senator was gonna wear dark brown tonight.

70
00:02:38,260 --> 00:02:39,700
I'm sure it'll be fine.

71
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:42,300
My husband is sponsoring a fundraiser tonight

72
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:43,900
for local dog shelters.

73
00:02:43,900 --> 00:02:47,100
Robert, California bought two tables for everyone here.

74
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:48,740
These people were lucky to get seats

75
00:02:48,740 --> 00:02:50,380
because it is gonna be a who's who

76
00:02:50,380 --> 00:02:52,140
of the Northern 22nd District.
